      "lesson title": "Embedding Sensitive Data in Models",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "In this lesson, you will explore how machine learning models can unintentionally absorb and later reveal sensitive information that was present in their training data. We will look at the ways that private details such as passwords, personal identifiers, and confidential records can become embedded within a model without any deliberate intention to store them. You will learn why this happens, what risks it creates for individuals and organisations, and how seemingly harmless model outputs can sometimes expose secrets that were never meant to be shared. By the end of the lesson, you will have a clearer understanding of why careful data handling before and during training is so important for protecting sensitive information.",
