          "subtitle": "Practical steps to protect your data",
          "slidecontent": "• Avoid training on data that contains real credentials, tokens, or personal identifiers\n• Scrub sensitive values before they ever reach your dataset\n• Use synthetic data where possible\n• Apply differential privacy techniques to limit how much any single example influences the model\n• Audit model outputs regularly for signs of memorised content\n• Treat data minimisation as a first principle, not an afterthought"
