          "number": 8,
          "slidetitle": "Key Points to Remember",
          "subtitle": "Core principles to keep in mind",
          "slidecontent": "• Models can memorise sensitive data if it appears repeatedly or in a distinctive pattern during training\n• Even well-intentioned training pipelines can accidentally bake in secrets\n• Scrubbing data before training is far more reliable than trying to fix leakage afterwards\n• Membership inference and extraction attacks are real, practical threats\n• Anonymisation alone is rarely enough\n• As a next step, audit any datasets you plan to use and remove credentials, personal details, and proprietary information before they ever reach a model"
